<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871231-0007 </DOCNO><HL> Credit Ratings</HL><DD> 12/31/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> ECBOND MARKET NEWS (BON) </IN><DATELINE> ENGELHARD CORP.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Standard andamp; Poor's Corp. cut the rating on $100 million of senior debt to single-A from single-A-plus. The rating concern cited Engelhard's plan to buy KaiserTech Ltd.'s Harshaw/Filtrol Partnership, which includes several specialty chemical businesses, for $264 million. The purchase by the Edison, N.J.-based specialty chemicals and metallurgical products company would reduce liquidity, Sandamp;P said. KaiserTech, Oakland, Calif., is the parent of Kaiser Aluminum andamp; Chemical Corp. Sandamp;P said Engelhard's debt rating is &quot;aided by its excess internal cash generating capability and undervalued precious metal inventory.&quot; A spokesman for Engelhard said, &quot;The single-A rating is certainly . . . very strong.&quot; </TEXT></DOC>